The paper deals with network functions virtualization (NFV) in large-scale datacenters (LDCs), which involves the optimization of traffic load balancing and scaling of virtual network functions (VNFs). This falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes a distributed approach based on Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers (ADMM), which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and optimization and control (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses linear programming (LP) models and Mixed Integer Linear Programming (MILP) models, which fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
